This work stands on prior open-source and academic contributions to the
MCP / FHIR / clinical-decision-support ecosystem. It does NOT redistribute
their code, but its design draws on:

- arXiv:2506.13800 — "Enhancing Clinical Decision Support and EHR Insights
  through LLMs and the Model Context Protocol: An Open-Source MCP-FHIR
  Framework" (Ehtesham, Singh, Kumar; 2025). The Bundle-prefetch +
  evaluation-on-r4.smarthealthit.org pattern is borrowed from this work.

- WSO2 fhir-mcp-server (Apache-2.0). General shape of an MCP server
  exposing FHIR resources; we layer rule-scoring on top instead of
  reimplementing the FHIR query surface.

- the-momentum/fhir-mcp-server (Apache-2.0). Reference for natural-language
  FHIR query patterns; complementary to this Superpower (queries fetch the
  Bundle; we score it).

- AWS HealthLake MCP Server (Apache-2.0). Reference for cloud-FHIR
  integration patterns and tool granularity.

- Innovaccer HMCP proposal. Influence on healthcare-specific MCP extension
  fields (auth, audit, governance) reflected in our SHARP envelope helpers.

- HL7 CDS Hooks 1.0 specification (https://cds-hooks.org/). The
  ``indicator`` vocabulary, ``card`` shape, and ``/cds-services`` discovery
  endpoint are taken verbatim from the standard.

- HL7 FHIR R4 specification. Patient, Encounter, Condition, Observation,
  AllergyIntolerance, DocumentReference resource shapes used in fixtures
  and test bundles.

- MDCalc (https://www.mdcalc.com/). Decision-rule cutoffs and
  interpretation language. We reference MDCalc URLs for each rule but do
  NOT redistribute MDCalc data; rule scoring tables are entered manually
  from primary literature and the rule is bundled under our Apache-2.0
  license.

- OpenEM / Tintinalli / Rosen / SAEM curricula. The selection of which
  decision rules to include reflects the published ED clinical-rules
  curriculum. No copyrighted content is included.

Decision-rule citations (validation-cohort papers) for each bundled rule
are linked in the rule's ``url`` field; full bibliography is kept in the
project's MODEL_CARD when published.

